contactmanager

Class ContactImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • contactmanager.ContactImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contact, Serializable

    public class ContactImpl
extends Object
implements Contact, Serializable
    A contact is a person we are making business with or may do in the future. Contacts have an ID (unique), a name (probably unique, but maybe not), and notes that the user may want to save about them.
    Since:
    24 February 2015
    Author:
    Oliver Smart <osmart01@dcs.bbk.ac.uk>
    See Also:
    Contact, Serialized Form
